%N A390090 Irregular triangle read by rows where row n lists the first differences of the binary indices of n.
%C A390090 Rows 0, 1, 2, are empty, so offset is 3.
%C A390090 A binary index of n is any position of a 1 in its reversed binary expansion. The binary indices of n are row n of A048793.
%e A390090 The binary indices of 27 are {1,2,4,5}, so row n = 27 is (1,2,1).
